Lecturer Performance Review & Feedback System
1. Problem Definition:
Universities need a way to :~
-Collect anonymous feedback about lecturers from students 
-Evaluate lecturers performance using quantitive scores and qualitative comments(for simplicity we'll only use quantititive socres )
-Generate reports that departments can use for improvements

2. Key Users
i. Lecturers:
After each class a lecturer will login to the system with the LECTURER's role and generate a feedback form which will be sent the student emails or a link copied and shared manually
Lecturers will be able to view their performance trends once they login to the system

ii. Students:
They receive the feedback form from via email or shared from a member as a link
After filling the form, it is submitted and the response stored as data in the databse
iii. Admin
View all reports and analytics dashboard
Export data to pdf or excel
Manage courses lecturers and departments



MVP: Lecturer Feedback Collection System

A simple system where:
Lecturers create feedback forms
Students fill feedback
Admin views reports

Lecturers view their own performance trends

1. MVP Features
A. Lecturer Features

Login as Lecturer
Create a new Feedback Form for a course - Generates a shareable link OR sends link via email
View feedback results (average score)
View performance trend (previous forms + their average score)

B. Student Features

Receive feedback form link (via email or shared manually)
Open the form (public link — no login required)
Rate the lecturer (e.g., 1–5 scale for 3–5 metrics)
Submit response → stored in database anonymously

C. Admin Features

Login as Admin
Manage: Lecturers, Courses, Departments
View all feedback data in a simple dashboard
Export: PDF report, Excel report

===============================================================
System Functional Requirements
==============================================================

Here are the core functional requirements written clearly.

A. Authentication Requirements
System must allow:
Admin login
Lecturer login
Students do not need to log in.

B. Lecturer Functional Requirements
Lecturer can create a new feedback form.
System generates a unique link to the form.
Lecturer can copy the link OR send it via email.
Lecturer can view: - Total number of student responses, Average rating per metric, Overall average rating
Lecturer can view performance trend as a simple line graph.

C. Student Functional Requirements
Student opens feedback form without login.
Student sees: Course, Lecturer name, 1–5 rating scale for metrics (e.g., clarity, engagement, explanation, preparedness)
Student submits response.
System stores response anonymously.
Students cannot edit submission after sending.

D. Admin Functional Requirements

Admin can add/edit/delete: Lecturers, Courses, Departments
Admin can assign courses to lecturers.
Admin can view all feedback submitted across the system.
Admin can export data as: PDF (summary), Excel (raw data)
Admin can generate system-wide analytics: Top lecturers, Average scores by department, Total responses per course.

===============================================================
Data Flow (How the system works)
------------------------------------
Step 1 — Lecturer logs in

→ Creates a feedback form
→ System generates a unique link, e.g.:

https://feedback.app/form/72hg278bhdb

Step 2 — Lecturer shares link

Either via email OR WhatsApp group OR LMS

Step 3 — Student fills form

Opens link
Rates lecturer (1–5)
Clicks submit
Data stored anonymously

Step 4 — Lecturer views results

Login again
Dashboard shows:
averages

number of submissions

trend graph

Step 5 — Admin views everything

Export reports

Manage lecturers, courses, departments


MVP Screens / Pages
For Lecturers: Login page, Dashboard, “Create Feedback Form” page, “My Results” page, “Performance Trend” chart. 

For Students: Feedback form page only.

For Admin: Admin login page, Admin dashboard, Manage Departments, Manage Lecturers, Manage Courses, View All Feedback, Export Reports

MVP API Endpoints
Lecturer APIs: 

POST /login
POST /feedback/create
GET /feedback/:lecturerId/results
GET /feedback/:lecturerId/trends

Student APIs:

GET /form/:id
POST /form/:id/submit

Admin APIs

POST /admin/login
CRUD /admin/lecturers
CRUD /admin/courses
CRUD /admin/departments
GET /admin/reports
GET /admin/export/pdf
GET /admin/export/excel

TechStack: React + TailwindCSS + Axios + Recharts + pdfkit + json2csv/exceljs, Django(REST Framework)

